<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>{{.Config.CADisplay}} — {{.Config.CeremonyType.Title}}</title>
<style>
:root {
  --accent: #1a3a5c;
  --accent-light: #2563a8;
  --border: #d1d5db;
  --code-bg: #1e1e2e;
  --code-fg: #cdd6f4;
  --code-comment: #6c7086;
  --warn-bg: #fff7ed;
  --warn-border: #fed7aa;
  --warn-text: #7c2d12;
  --ok-bg: #f0fdf4;
  --ok-border: #bbf7d0;
  --ok-text: #166534;
}
* { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
body {
  font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
  font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: #111;
  background: #fff; padding: 40px 56px; max-width: 960px; margin: 0 auto;
}
.cover { text-align: center; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent); padding-bottom: 32px; margin-bottom: 32px; }
.classification {
  display: inline-block; background: var(--accent); color: #fff;
  font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
  padding: 3px 14px; border-radius: 3px; margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.cover h1 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 6px; }
.cover h2 { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; color: #4b5563; margin-bottom: 20px; }
.meta-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 140px 1fr; gap: 6px 16px; text-align: left; max-width: 480px; margin: 0 auto; font-size: 13px; }
.meta-grid .key { color: #6b7280; font-weight: 600; }
h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--accent); margin: 28px 0 10px; padding-bottom: 4px; border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb; page-break-after: avoid; }
h4 { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; color: #374151; margin: 16px 0 6px; }
p { font-size: 13px; color: #374151; margin-bottom: 8px; }
ul, ol { padding-left: 20px; font-size: 13px; color: #374151; margin-bottom: 8px; }
li { margin-bottom: 4px; }
.checklist { list-style: none; padding-left: 0; }
.checklist li { display: flex; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 6px; font-size: 13px; }
.checklist li::before { content: "☐"; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.4; flex-shrink: 0; color: #6b7280; }
pre {
  background: var(--code-bg); color: var(--code-fg);
  font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Cascadia Code', 'Fira Code', monospace;
  font-size: 12px; border-radius: 6px; padding: 14px 16px; margin: 10px 0;
  overflow-x: auto; white-space: pre; line-height: 1.7;
  page-break-inside: avoid;
}
.comment { color: var(--code-comment); }
.step {
  background: #f7f8fa; border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-light);
  border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0; padding: 12px 16px; margin: 10px 0;
  page-break-inside: avoid;
}
.step-num { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--accent-light); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .06em; margin-bottom: 4px; }
.warn {
  background: var(--warn-bg); border: 1px solid var(--warn-border);
  border-radius: 6px; padding: 12px 14px; margin: 10px 0; font-size: 13px; color: var(--warn-text);
}
.warn strong { display: block; margin-bottom: 2px; }
.ok {
  background: var(--ok-bg); border: 1px solid var(--ok-border);
  border-radius: 6px; padding: 10px 14px; margin: 8px 0; font-size: 13px; color: var(--ok-text);
}
table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 13px; margin: 10px 0; }
th { text-align: left; padding: 6px 10px; background: #f3f4f6; border: 1px solid var(--border); font-weight: 600; font-size: 12px; }
td { padding: 7px 10px; border: 1px solid var(--border); vertical-align: top; }
.sig-line { border-bottom: 1px solid #374151; min-height: 28px; }
.mono { font-family: monospace; font-size: 11px; color: #6b7280; }
.page-break { page-break-after: always; }

.notes { margin: 14px 0; page-break-inside: avoid; }
.notes strong { font-size: 12px; color: #6b7280; display: block; margin-bottom: 4px; }
.notes-area {
  border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 4px; min-height: 80px;
  background: #fafafa;
}

@media print {
  body { padding: 15mm 20mm; }
  pre { background: #f8f8f8 !important; color: #111 !important; border: 1px solid #ccc; }
  .comment { color: #666 !important; }
  .notes-area { min-height: 100px; background: #fff !important; border: 1px solid #999; }
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ── COVER ── -->
<div class="cover">
  <div class="classification">Key Ceremony Procedure</div>
  <h1>{{.Config.OrgDisplay}}</h1>
  <h2>{{.Config.CADisplay}} · {{.Config.CeremonyType.Title}}</h2>
  <div class="meta-grid">
    <span class="key">Date</span>          <span>{{.Config.Date}}</span>
    <span class="key">Location</span>      <span>{{.Config.LocationDisplay}}</span>
    <span class="key">Operator</span>      <span>{{.Config.OperatorDisplay}}</span>
    <span class="key">Custodians</span>    <span>{{.Config.Shamir.Shares}} (threshold: any {{.Config.Shamir.Threshold}})</span>
    <span class="key">Document Ver.</span> <span>1.0 — Generated {{.GeneratedAt}} UTC</span>
    <span class="key">Standards</span>     <span>EN 319 401 §7.5/7.6 · TS 119 431-1 V1.3.1</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ── 1. PURPOSE ── -->
<h3>1 · Purpose and Scope</h3>
<p>{{.CeremonyDescription}}</p>
<p>This ceremony is performed in accordance with <strong>ETSI EN 319 401 V3.2.1 §7.5</strong> (Cryptographic Controls) and <strong>§7.6</strong> (Physical and Environmental Security). The Shamir Secret Sharing implementation is <strong>ssss</strong> (B. Poettering). Share encryption uses <strong>age</strong> with <strong>age-plugin-yubikey</strong> (str4d).</p>
<div class="warn">
  <strong>⚠ This is a security-sensitive ceremony.</strong>
  All commands shall be executed only by the designated Operator in the presence of all custodians and witnesses.
  No part of this ceremony shall be performed outside the designated secure room.
  All mobile phones and networked devices must be removed before the ceremony begins.
</div>

<!-- ── 2. PERSONNEL ── -->
<h3>2 · Personnel</h3>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Role</th><th>Name</th><th>Signature</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>Ceremony Operator</td><td>{{.Config.OperatorDisplay}}</td><td class="sig-line"></td></tr>
    {{range $i, $c := .Config.Custodians}}<tr><td>Custodian {{add $i 1}}</td><td>{{$.Config.CustodianName $i}}</td><td class="sig-line"></td></tr>
    {{end}}{{range $i, $w := .Config.Witnesses}}<tr><td>Witness {{add $i 1}}</td><td>{{$.Config.WitnessName $i}}</td><td class="sig-line"></td></tr>
    {{end}}
  </tbody>
</table>

<!-- ── 3. PRE-CEREMONY CHECKLIST ── -->
<h3>3 · Pre-Ceremony Checklist</h3>

<h4>3.1 Personnel Verification</h4>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li>All {{.Config.Shamir.Shares}} custodians physically present — identity verified with government-issued photo ID</li>
  <li>All {{len .Config.Witnesses}} witnesses physically present</li>
  <li>Ceremony operator present</li>
  <li>No additional personnel in the room</li>
  <li>All mobile phones and wireless devices removed from the room</li>
</ul>

<h4>3.2 Equipment</h4>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li>Air-gapped laptop — no WiFi hardware, or disabled at BIOS level; no network cable connected</li>
  <li>Booted from verified read-only media (Tails OS recommended) or freshly installed offline OS</li>
  <li>{{.Config.Shamir.Shares}} × YubiKey 5 Series (one per custodian) — factory-reset or known-good state</li>
  {{if .IncludeUSBDrives}}<li>{{mul .Config.Shamir.Shares .USBDrivesPerShare}} × dedicated USB drives ({{.USBDrivesPerShare}} per custodian, labelled Custodian N — Copy 1/{{.USBDrivesPerShare}} through {{.USBDrivesPerShare}}/{{.USBDrivesPerShare}}, never previously used)</li>{{end}}
  <li>Video camera for ceremony recording — mandatory audit trail per EN 319 401 §7.6-13</li>
  {{if .IsYubiHSM}}<li>2 × YubiHSM 2 FIPS (serial numbers recorded below) for CA key storage</li>{{end}}
  {{if .IsPKCS11}}<li>PKCS#11 HSM device (or SoftHSM 2 for testing) — module: <code>{{.Config.PKCS11.ModulePath}}</code></li>{{end}}
  <li>Printed copy of this ceremony script (this document)</li>
  <li>Printed log sheets for recording ceremony artifacts</li>
  <li>Permanent markers for labelling USB drives</li>
  {{if .IncludeUSBDrives}}<li>{{mul .Config.Shamir.Shares .USBDrivesPerShare}} × tamper-evident bags (one per USB drive)</li>{{end}}
</ul>

<h4>3.3 Software (verify hashes before ceremony)</h4>
{{codeblock .VerifySoftwareCmd}}
<ul class="checklist">
  <li>ssss installed — <code>apt install ssss</code> / <code>brew install ssss</code></li>
  <li>age installed — <code>apt install age</code> / <code>brew install age</code></li>
  <li>age-plugin-yubikey installed — binary from <code>github.com/str4d/age-plugin-yubikey/releases</code></li>
  <li>ykman installed — <code>apt install yubikey-manager</code></li>
  {{if .IsYubiHSM}}<li>yubihsm-shell installed — from Yubico packages</li>{{end}}
  {{if .IsPKCS11}}<li>softhsm2-util and pkcs11-tool (OpenSC) installed</li>{{end}}
  <li>All version strings recorded in ceremony log</li>
</ul>

<h4>3.4 Video Recording</h4>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li>Camera positioned to show the screen and all personnel — the ceremony is designed so that secret material is never displayed on screen</li>
  <li>Recording started — announce on camera: organisation, CA name, ceremony type, date, time, location, and all personnel present by name and role</li>
</ul>

<!-- ── 4. ENVIRONMENT SETUP ── -->
<h3>4 · Environment Setup</h3>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-num">Step 1</div>
  <strong>Verify Air-Gap</strong>
  <p>The operator confirms on camera that the workstation has no network connectivity.</p>
  {{codeblock .AirGapCmd}}
  <ul class="checklist">
    <li>All network interfaces confirmed DOWN or absent</li>
    <li>Wireless hardware disabled and confirmed by physical inspection</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-num">Step 2</div>
  <strong>Prepare Working Directory</strong>
  {{codeblock .PrepWorkdirCmd}}
  <ul class="checklist">
    <li>Working directory confirmed on tmpfs (RAM only — no disk writes)</li>
  </ul>
</div>

{{if .IsYubiHSM}}
<div class="step">
  <div class="step-num">Step 3</div>
  <strong>Verify YubiHSM Devices</strong>
  {{codeblock .VerifyYubiHSMCmd}}
  <ul class="checklist">
    <li>YubiHSM 2 FIPS device #1 detected — Serial No.: __________</li>
    <li>YubiHSM 2 FIPS device #2 detected — Serial No.: __________</li>
    <li>Both devices confirmed FIPS 140-2 Level 3 (Cert #3916)</li>
  </ul>
</div>
{{end}}

{{if .IsPKCS11}}
<div class="step">
  <div class="step-num">Step 3</div>
  <strong>Initialise PKCS#11 Token</strong>
  <p>Initialise the PKCS#11 token. Set the SO PIN and User PIN when prompted. Record both PINs in the ceremony log.</p>
  {{codeblock .VerifyPKCS11Cmd}}
  <ul class="checklist">
    <li>PKCS#11 module loaded: <code>{{.Config.PKCS11.ModulePath}}</code></li>
    <li>Token label: <code>{{.Config.PKCS11.TokenLabel}}</code></li>
    <li>SO PIN set and recorded securely</li>
    <li>User PIN set and recorded securely</li>
  </ul>
</div>
{{end}}

<!-- ── 5. YUBIKEY ENROLLMENT ── -->
<h3>5 · Custodian YubiKey Enrollment</h3>
<p>Each custodian's YubiKey is enrolled with a PIV key used as the age recipient for their SSS share. Complete this for all {{.Config.Shamir.Shares}} custodians before generating the secret.</p>
<div class="warn">
  <strong>⚠ One YubiKey at a time.</strong>
  Only one YubiKey should be inserted during each enrollment step.
  After enrollment, remove the YubiKey and return it to the custodian immediately.
</div>

{{range $i, $_ := .Config.Custodians}}
<h4>Custodian {{add $i 1}}: {{$.Config.CustodianName $i}}</h4>
<p>Insert {{$.Config.CustodianName $i}}'s YubiKey into the workstation's USB port.</p>
{{codeblock (index $.EnrollCmds $i)}}
<div class="ok">☑ Record in ceremony log — Custodian {{add $i 1}} · YubiKey Serial No.: __________ · age recipient: <code>age1yubikey1___________</code></div>
<p>Remove {{$.Config.CustodianName $i}}'s YubiKey before proceeding to the next custodian.</p>
{{end}}

<div class="ok">☑ Verification: All {{.Config.Shamir.Shares}} custodian age recipient strings recorded in ceremony log before proceeding.</div>

<!-- ── 6. SECRET GENERATION ── -->
{{if not .IsRecovery}}
<h3>6 · Secret Generation</h3>

{{if .IsHSMKeygen}}
<p>The Root CA private key is generated directly inside the YubiHSM 2 FIPS device. The wrap key is generated separately to enable encrypted key backup.</p>
<div class="step">
  <div class="step-num">Step 6a</div>
  <strong>Generate Root CA Key Inside YubiHSM</strong>
  {{codeblock .GenerateHSMKeyCmd}}
</div>
<div class="step">
  <div class="step-num">Step 6b</div>
  <strong>Generate Wrap Key for Backup</strong>
  {{codeblock .GenerateKeyCmd}}
</div>
{{else}}
<p>A 256-bit random wrap key is generated using the OS CSPRNG (<code>/dev/urandom</code>). This key enables decryption of exported CA key backups and will be split using Shamir Secret Sharing.</p>
<div class="step">
  <div class="step-num">Step 6</div>
  <strong>Generate Wrap Key</strong>
  {{codeblock .GenerateKeyCmd}}
  <ul class="checklist">
    <li>Key length confirmed: 64 hex characters (256 bits)</li>
    <li>First 4 and last 4 hex chars confirmed by all witnesses (full key is never shown on screen)</li>
  </ul>
  <div class="notes">
    <strong>Notes</strong>
    <div class="notes-area"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="warn">
    <strong>⚠ Proceed immediately to Section 7.</strong>
    Do not leave the terminal unattended. The wrap key must not be written to disk or transmitted. It exists only in RAM.
  </div>
</div>
{{end}}

<!-- ── 7. SSS SPLIT ── -->
<h3>7 · Shamir Secret Sharing — Split ({{.Config.Shamir.Threshold}}-of-{{.Config.Shamir.Shares}})</h3>
<div class="warn">
  <strong>⚠ All {{.Config.Shamir.Shares}} custodians must be present during this step.</strong>
  Share values are written directly to individual files and are never displayed on screen.
  This is the most sensitive moment of the ceremony.
</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-num">Step 7</div>
  <strong>Split Secret into {{.Config.Shamir.Shares}} Shares</strong>
  {{codeblock .SSSSplitCmd}}
  <p>Shares are written directly to individual files. Record share numbers (NOT values) in the ceremony log.</p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Share #</th><th>Assigned Custodian</th><th>Confirmed Written ☑</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      {{range $i, $_ := .Config.Custodians}}<tr>
        <td>{{add $i 1}}</td>
        <td>{{$.Config.CustodianName $i}}</td>
        <td>☐</td>
      </tr>
      {{end}}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <div class="notes">
    <strong>Notes</strong>
    <div class="notes-area"></div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ── 8. SHARE ENCRYPTION ── -->
<h3>8 · Share Encryption</h3>
<p>Each share is encrypted to its custodian's YubiKey using <code>age</code>. The custodian's physical YubiKey and PIN are required at reconstruction time; the encrypted file alone is useless without the device.</p>

{{range $i, $_ := .Config.Custodians}}
<h4>Encrypt Share {{add $i 1}} → {{$.Config.CustodianName $i}}</h4>
{{codeblock (index $.EncryptCmds $i)}}
{{if $.IncludeUSBDrives}}
<p>Copy <code>custodian{{add $i 1}}.share.age</code> to each of {{$.USBDrivesPerShare}} dedicated USB drives for Custodian {{add $i 1}}. Eject each drive and place in a separate tamper-evident bag.</p>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Copy</th><th>USB Label</th><th>Storage Location</th><th>Copied ☑</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    {{range $d := seq $.USBDrivesPerShare}}<tr>
      <td>{{$d}}/{{$.USBDrivesPerShare}}</td>
      <td class="mono">Custodian {{add $i 1}} — Copy {{$d}}</td>
      <td>__________</td>
      <td>☐</td>
    </tr>
    {{end}}
  </tbody>
</table>
{{end}}
{{end}}

<div class="ok">☑ All {{.Config.Shamir.Shares}} custodian share files encrypted and distributed.</div>

{{end}}{{/* end if not IsRecovery */}}

{{if .IsRecovery}}
<!-- ── RECOVERY PATH ── -->
<h3>6 · Share Decryption and Reconstruction</h3>
<p>At least {{.Config.Shamir.Threshold}} custodians must present their YubiKey to decrypt their share. The Operator collects the decrypted values and combines them.</p>

{{range $i := .RecoveryCustodians}}
<h4>Custodian {{add $i 1}}: {{$.Config.CustodianName $i}} — Decrypt Share</h4>
<p>Insert {{$.Config.CustodianName $i}}'s YubiKey. Enter PIV PIN when prompted.</p>
{{codeblock (index $.RecoveryDecryptCmds $i)}}
<p>Remove {{$.Config.CustodianName $i}}'s YubiKey after decryption.</p>
{{end}}

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-num">Step 7</div>
  <strong>Reconstruct Secret</strong>
  {{codeblock .RecoveryCombineCmd}}
</div>
{{end}}

<!-- ── 9. VERIFICATION ── -->
{{if and .Config.Options.IncludeVerification (not .IsRecovery)}}
<h3>9 · Verification</h3>
<div class="warn"><strong>⚠ All custodians must remain in the room during verification.</strong></div>
<p>Before destroying plaintext material, verify that {{.Config.Shamir.Threshold}} shares reconstruct the original secret.</p>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-num">Step 9a</div>
  <strong>Test Reconstruction with {{.Config.Shamir.Threshold}} Shares</strong>
  {{codeblock .VerifyReconstructCmd}}
  <ul class="checklist">
    <li>Reconstructed secret matches original wrap key — confirmed by automated comparison (no secrets shown on screen)</li>
    <li>Test share files wiped immediately: <code>shred -u share*.txt</code></li>
  </ul>
  <div class="notes">
    <strong>Notes</strong>
    <div class="notes-area"></div>
  </div>
</div>

{{if .IncludeHSM}}
{{if .IsYubiHSM}}
<div class="step">
  <div class="step-num">Step 9b</div>
  <strong>Import Wrap Key into YubiHSM (both devices)</strong>
  {{codeblock .ImportWrapKeyCmd}}
  <ul class="checklist">
    <li>Wrap key object (ID 0x0100) confirmed on YubiHSM #1 (SN: __________)</li>
    <li>Wrap key object (ID 0x0100) confirmed on YubiHSM #2 (SN: __________)</li>
  </ul>
</div>
{{end}}
{{if .IsPKCS11}}
<div class="step">
  <div class="step-num">Step 9b</div>
  <strong>Import Wrap Key into PKCS#11 Token</strong>
  {{codeblock .ImportWrapKeyCmd}}
  <ul class="checklist">
    <li>Wrap key object confirmed in token <code>{{.Config.PKCS11.TokenLabel}}</code></li>
    <li>Temporary binary file shredded</li>
  </ul>
</div>
{{end}}
{{end}}
{{end}}

<!-- ── 10. SECURE CLEANUP ── -->
<h3>{{.CleanupSectionNum}} · Secure Cleanup</h3>
<div class="warn"><strong>⚠ This step is mandatory and must not be skipped.</strong> All plaintext key material must be destroyed before leaving the secure room.</div>

<div class="step">
  <div class="step-num">Step {{.CleanupSectionNum}}</div>
  <strong>Wipe All Plaintext Material</strong>
  {{codeblock .CleanupCmd}}
  <ul class="checklist">
    <li>All files in /tmp/ceremony securely wiped (shred confirmed)</li>
    <li>Shell history cleared</li>
    <li>WRAP_KEY and all C<em>N</em>_RECIPIENT variables unset</li>
    <li>Terminal window closed</li>
    <li>Workstation powered off (not suspended or hibernated)</li>
    <li>Video recording stopped — confirm saved to ceremony archive</li>
  </ul>
  <div class="notes">
    <strong>Notes</strong>
    <div class="notes-area"></div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ── 11. CEREMONY RECORD ── -->
<h3>{{.RecordSectionNum}} · Ceremony Record</h3>
<p>Record the following in the formal ceremony log. Retain for a minimum of <strong>7 years</strong> after the associated CA certificate ceases to be valid (TS 119 431-1 §6.4.6).</p>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>Organisation</td><td>{{.Config.OrgDisplay}}</td></tr>
    <tr><td>CA Name</td><td>{{.Config.CADisplay}}</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Ceremony Type</td><td>{{.Config.CeremonyType.Title}}</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Date and Time</td><td>{{.Config.Date}} ____:____ UTC</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Location</td><td>{{.Config.LocationDisplay}}</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Operator</td><td>{{.Config.OperatorDisplay}}</td></tr>
    <tr><td>SSS Parameters</td><td>{{.Config.Shamir.Threshold}}-of-{{.Config.Shamir.Shares}}</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Share Storage</td><td>{{.StorageNote}}</td></tr>
    {{if .IsYubiHSM}}
    <tr><td>HSM Type</td><td>YubiHSM 2 FIPS</td></tr>
    <tr><td>YubiHSM #1 Serial</td><td>__________</td></tr>
    <tr><td>YubiHSM #2 Serial</td><td>__________</td></tr>
    {{end}}
    {{if .IsPKCS11}}
    <tr><td>HSM Type</td><td>PKCS#11 — {{.Config.PKCS11.ModulePath}}</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Token Label</td><td>{{.Config.PKCS11.TokenLabel}}</td></tr>
    {{end}}
    {{if not .IncludeHSM}}
    <tr><td>HSM Type</td><td>None</td></tr>
    {{end}}
    <tr><td>Video Recording Reference</td><td>__________</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h4>Custodian Share Assignment</h4>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Custodian</th><th>YubiKey Serial</th><th>age Recipient (first 24 chars)</th><th>Share File</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    {{range $i, $_ := .Config.Custodians}}<tr>
      <td>{{add $i 1}}</td>
      <td>{{$.Config.CustodianName $i}}</td>
      <td>__________</td>
      <td class="mono">age1yubikey1____________…</td>
      <td class="mono">custodian{{add $i 1}}.share.age</td>
    </tr>
    {{end}}
  </tbody>
</table>

<!-- ── SIGNATURE PAGE ── -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h3>{{.SigSectionNum}} · Signature Page</h3>
<p>By signing below, each party confirms that they were present throughout the ceremony, that it was conducted in accordance with this procedure, and that the ceremony log accurately reflects what occurred.</p>

<h4>Ceremony Operator</h4>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Name</th><th>Signature</th><th>Date</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody><tr><td>{{.Config.OperatorDisplay}}</td><td class="sig-line"></td><td class="sig-line"></td></tr></tbody>
</table>

<h4>Custodians</h4>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Name</th><th>YubiKey Serial</th><th>Signature</th><th>Share Received ☑</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    {{range $i, $_ := .Config.Custodians}}<tr>
      <td>{{add $i 1}}</td>
      <td>{{$.Config.CustodianName $i}}</td>
      <td>__________</td>
      <td class="sig-line"></td>
      <td>☐</td>
    </tr>
    {{end}}
